{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T08:11:27.281Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Inverted Dropout"},{"type":"text","text":" is the standard implementation of dropout that performs scaling "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"during training"},{"type":"text","text":" instead of during testing. By dividing activations by the keep probability "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"p"}},{"type":"text","text":" during training, it ensures the expected output value remains the same whether dropout is applied or not, making the network behavior "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"consistent"},{"type":"text","text":" between training and inference without any test-time adjustments."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Inverted Dropout Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Inverted dropout is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"implementation technique"},{"type":"text","text":" for dropout regularization:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Standard dropout"},{"type":"text","text":": Scale activations at "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"test time"},{"type":"text","text":" (multiply by keep probability)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Inverted dropout"},{"type":"text","text":": Scale activations at "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"training time"},{"type":"text","text":" (divide by keep probability)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why \"inverted\"?"},{"type":"text","text":" - Traditional dropout: \"Drop at train, scale at test\"\n- Inverted dropout: \"Drop "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"and"},{"type":"text","text":" scale at train, nothing at test\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How Inverted Dropout Works: Step-by-Step"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Training Phase"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Given:\n# activations a = [0.5, 0.8, 0.3, 0.9, 0.2, 0.7]\n# dropout_rate = 0.2 (20% dropped)\n# keep_prob p = 0.8 (80% kept)\n\n# Step 1: Generate dropout mask\nmask = [1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 0]  # random: 1=keep, 0=drop\n\n# Step 2: Apply mask (element-wise multiply)\na_masked = a * mask = [0.5, 0.8, 0, 0.9, 0.2, 0]\n\n# Step 3: Scale UP during training (inverted dropout!)\na_dropout = a_masked / p = [0.5/0.8, 0.8/0.8, 0/0.8, 0.9/0.8, 0.2/0.8, 0/0.8]\n          = [0.625, 1.0, 0, 1.125, 0.25, 0]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": Scaling by "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"1/p"}},{"type":"text","text":" boosts remaining neurons to compensate for dropped ones."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Testing/Inference Phase"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# No dropout, no scaling needed!\na_test = a  # Just use original activations directly"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Advantage"},{"type":"text","text":": Test code is simpler — no scaling logic to remember."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Math: Why Inverted Dropout Works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Expected Value Preservation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Goal"},{"type":"text","text":": The expected activation value should be the same whether dropout is applied or not."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Without dropout"},{"type":"text","text":":\n\\[\nE[a"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"{\\text{no dropout}}] = a\n\\]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"With standard dropout"},{"type":"text","text":" (no scaling):\n- Neuron kept with probability "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"p"}},{"type":"text","text":": output = "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"a"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Neuron dropped with probability "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"1-p"}},{"type":"text","text":": output = "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"0"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n\\[\nE[a"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"{\\text{dropout}}] = p \\cdot a + (1-p) \\cdot 0 = p \\cdot a\n\\]"}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"**Problem**: Expected value is \\( p \\cdot a \\), which is **smaller** than \\( a \\) (e.g., if \\( p=0.8 \\), expected value is 80% of original). [reddit](https://www.reddit.com/r/MachineLearning/comments/6edku6/d_inverted_dropout_how_does_it_really_work/)"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"With inverted dropout"},{"type":"text","text":" (scale by "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"1/p"}},{"type":"text","text":"):\n- Neuron kept with probability "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"p"}},{"type":"text","text":": output = "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\frac{a}{p}"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Neuron dropped with probability "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"1-p"}},{"type":"text","text":": output = "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"0"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n\\[\nE[a"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"{\\text{inverted}}] = p \\cdot \\frac{a}{p} + (1-p) \\cdot 0 = a\n\\]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":": Expected value = "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"a"}},{"type":"text","text":", same as without dropout!"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Standard Dropout vs. Inverted Dropout: Math Comparison"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Standard Dropout (Original Hinton Method)"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Phase"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Operation"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Formula"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Training"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Drop neurons only"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"a_{\\text{train}} = a \\cdot m"}},{"type":"text","text":" (no scaling)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Testing"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scale activations"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"a_{\\text{test}} = a \\cdot p"}},{"type":"text","text":" (multiply by keep prob)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Problem"},{"type":"text","text":": Must remember to scale at test time → error-prone."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Inverted Dropout (Modern Standard)"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Phase"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Operation"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Formula"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Training"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Drop "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"and"},{"type":"text","text":" scale"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"a_{\\text{train}} = \\frac{a \\cdot m}{p}"}}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Testing"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No operation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"a_{\\text{test}} = a"}},{"type":"text","text":" (use directly)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Advantage"},{"type":"text","text":": Test code simpler → no scaling logic needed."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual Comparison: What Happens to Activations"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scenario: 5 neurons, keep_prob = 0.8 (20% drop)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ORIGINAL ACTIVATIONS:\n[0.5, 0.8, 0.3, 0.9, 0.2]\n\nSTANDARD DROPOUT (training, no scaling):\nMask: [1, 0, 1, 1, 1]\nOutput: [0.5, 0, 0.3, 0.9, 0.2]\nMean: 0.38  ← reduced from 0.54 (original) ❌\n\nSTANDARD DROPOUT (testing, with scaling):\nMultiply by p=0.8:\nOutput: [0.4, 0, 0.24, 0.72, 0.16]\nMean: 0.304  ← now even smaller! (but matched to training) ✓\n\nINVERTED DROPOUT (training, with scaling):\nMask: [1, 0, 1, 1, 1]\nOutput: [0.5/0.8, 0, 0.3/0.8, 0.9/0.8, 0.2/0.8]\n      = [0.625, 0, 0.375, 1.125, 0.25]\nMean: 0.475  ← close to original 0.54 ✓\n\nINVERTED DROPOUT (testing, no scaling):\nOutput: [0.5, 0.8, 0.3, 0.9, 0.2] (directly)\nMean: 0.54  ← matches training expectation ✓"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": Inverted dropout keeps mean activation "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"stable"},{"type":"text","text":" across training/testing."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Inverted Dropout Is Better"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Consistent Network Behavior"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Standard Dropout"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Inverted Dropout"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Training mean activation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"p \\cdot a"}},{"type":"text","text":" (reduced)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"a"}},{"type":"text","text":" (preserved)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Testing mean activation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"p \\cdot a"}},{"type":"text","text":" (scaled)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"a"}},{"type":"text","text":" (original)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Consistency"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Matched"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Matched"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both achieve consistency, but inverted dropout does it "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"more naturally"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. No Test-Time Adjustment"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Standard dropout (error-prone):\n# Training\noutput = model(x_train)  # dropout active\n\n# Testing (must manually scale!)\noutput = model(x_test) * keep_prob  # ← easy to forget! ❌\n\n# Inverted dropout (clean):\n# Training\noutput = model(x_train)  # dropout active + scaling\n\n# Testing (no adjustment needed!)\noutput = model(x_test)  # ← simple ✅"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefit"},{"type":"text","text":": No risk of forgetting to scale at test time."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Stable Cost Function"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Inverted dropout keeps the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"magnitude of activations"},{"type":"text","text":" consistent:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Training: activations scaled up → expected value = original"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Testing: activations unchanged → same expected value"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cost function (loss) behaves consistently across phases"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefit"},{"type":"text","text":": Training dynamics more stable, easier to interpret."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Practical Implementation"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"PyTorch (Uses Inverted Dropout Internally)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import torch.nn as nn\n\nmodel = nn.Sequential(\n    nn.Linear(128, 256),\n    nn.Dropout(0.5),  # Inverted dropout built-in\n    nn.ReLU()\n)\n\n# Training\nmodel.train()  # Dropout active with inverted scaling\noutput = model(x)\n\n# Testing  \nmodel.eval()  # Dropout disabled, NO scaling needed\noutput = model(x)  # ← Clean, no manual adjustment"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"PyTorch's "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"nn.Dropout"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" uses inverted dropout"},{"type":"text","text":" by default."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"TensorFlow/Keras (Uses Inverted Dropout Internally)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"from tensorflow.keras import layers\n\nmodel = layers.Sequential([\n    layers.Dense(256, input_shape=(128,)),\n    layers.Dropout(0.5),  # Inverted dropout built-in\n    layers.ReLU()\n])\n\n# Training: automatically active\nmodel.fit(x_train, y_train)\n\n# Testing: automatically disabled\npredictions = model.predict(x_test)  # ← No scaling needed"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Keras also uses inverted dropout"},{"type":"text","text":" by default."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Manual Implementation (If Needed)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import numpy as np\n\ndef inverted_dropout(a, dropout_rate=0.5):\n    \"\"\"\n    Inverted dropout implementation\n    a: activations\n    dropout_rate: fraction to drop (e.g., 0.5 = 50%)\n    \"\"\"\n    keep_prob = 1 - dropout_rate\n    \n    # Step 1: Generate mask\n    mask = np.random.rand(*a.shape) < keep_prob\n    \n    # Step 2: Apply mask AND scale (inverted!)\n    a_dropout = a * mask / keep_prob\n    \n    return a_dropout\n\n# Training\na_dropout = inverted_dropout(a, dropout_rate=0.5)\n\n# Testing (no function call needed!)\na_test = a  # Direct usage"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Inverted dropout"},{"type":"text","text":" scales activations "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"during training"},{"type":"text","text":" (divide by "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"p"}},{"type":"text","text":") instead of testing"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Standard dropout"},{"type":"text","text":": Scale at test time (multiply by "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"p"}},{"type":"text","text":") → error-prone"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Expected value preserved"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"E[\\text{inverted}] = p \\cdot \\frac{a}{p} = a"}},{"type":"text","text":" (same as no dropout)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test code simpler"},{"type":"text","text":": No scaling logic needed → just use network directly"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Modern frameworks use it"},{"type":"text","text":": PyTorch "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"nn.Dropout"},{"type":"text","text":", Keras "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Dropout"},{"type":"text","text":" both use inverted dropout internally"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stable cost function"},{"type":"text","text":": Activations maintain consistent magnitude across training/testing"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mathematically equivalent"},{"type":"text","text":": Both methods achieve same expected value, but inverted is cleaner"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Inverted dropout is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"standard implementation"},{"type":"text","text":" in modern deep learning frameworks because it simplifies test-time code while maintaining mathematical equivalence to standard dropout."}]}]}}
